
"I'm to old for that." he said.
"Now." Maryse demanded.
Jace slowly picked himself up, and slow motion walked over to the door. Everyone waited for him, for they knew that if they moved to push him, he would put them in a head lock and mess up their hair.
Once he got out of the doorway, Maryse shut the door, shutting off the image of Jace, who had turned around and was starting to make faces.
"Now, who's going to help me fix a water fountain and help Simon?" she asked.